Job Description:
Symend is looking to hire a Business Systems Analyst for a variety of high-profile enterprise projects. The successful candidate will be responsible for understanding and documenting the business needs of our clients and stakeholders. The requirements will support the development of our treatment plans, our definition of key data elements, and the configuration of our platform. They will build rapport with and among all project stakeholders, instilling confidence in our ability to add value and meet project objectives. The BSA collaborates with the Strategy, Development and Client Services teams to leverage our platform to meet client requirements.
Responsibilities
Participates in and facilitates requirements gathering workshops and meetings to collect and map current client collection practices and identify potential opportunities to the leverage Symend;
Breaks down complicated business problems. Gathers, defines, analyzes and translates stakeholder requirements, data and technical constraints into various client facing and internal deliverables;
Collaborates with the Strategy, Development and Client Services team to document requirements and map solution options;
Engages clients and provides deep functional expertise of product capabilities to ensure treatment plans, product configuration and reporting commitments set the team up for success;
Responsible for presenting to management, internal/external stakeholders and project team to communicate systems/business capabilities and recommendations;
Acts as a customer advocate within Symend, driving customer-oriented solution design and supportive materials.
Qualifications
Post-Secondary Degree, preferable in Business Administration or Information Technology;
5+ years’ experience in Business Systems Analysis practice, preferably in a consulting environment delivering to enterprise clients;
Demonstrated experience in defining and documenting business requirements for business software development, integration, and or software product implementation projects;
Experience and knowledge of the collections’ industry is a definite asset.
All positions require background screening. This will include criminal and education checks to comply with regulations.
Required Skills
Ability to formulate concepts; communication of technical information to a non-technical audience; communication of business information to a technical audience;
Excellent analytical, problem identification and problem-solving skills;
Customer focused, sensitive to customer needs, their critical business cycles and schedules;
Advanced levels of facilitation, presentation, negotiation, and communication skills;
Excellent people skills; ability to work with other organizations and influence people outside of an authority relationship;
Entrepreneurial spirit suited for fast-paced, results-based environment, requiring flexibility to ever-changing needs;
Ability to work at a detailed level and quickly learn business application-specific details;
Highly self-motivated and able to work effectively with virtual teams of diverse background and cultures;
Confidence in self and organization, and a ‘can-do’ attitude in the face of change and ambiguity.
