About Symend
Symend is transforming the debt recovery industry by treating individuals with empathy and dignity at the time when they need it most. Combining behavioral science with advanced AI, data, and analytics capabilities, Symend’s customer engagement platform enables service providers and financial institutions to develop positive, individualized treatment programs for their at-risk customers. By approaching past-due customers with both evidence-based insight and compassion, Symend’s clients experience higher cure rates and reduced costs while building long-term relationships with customers and lifelong value for their companies and brands. Symend: The science of engagement.™

Job Title

Business Incentives, Sr. Analyst

Job Description Summary

The Business Incentives Senior Analyst works with a team to provide complex incentive consulting services to corporate clients. The Senior Analyst identifies incentive opportunities, provides related analysis for a variety of locations for each project and participates in the management of day-to-day client management activities. The Senior Analyst also identifies implications driven by client operations and works with management to develop solutions for each clients unique needs.

Job Description

Core Responsibilities:
Gather necessary project inputs and tax data from the client
Create project schedules, activities, resource plans and final reports;
Conduct original research into technical, practical, and procedural aspects of incentive programs and state and local corporate tax implications
Build and update complex opportunity analysis, including discounted cash flow models;
Analyze input data provided by clients and their external consultants and ensuring models accurately reflect this information;
Use Microsoft PowerPoint, Excel, and other applicable presentation tools;
Ensure presentations are clear, address client questions and goals;
Assist in presenting to clients, including attending client meetings;
Collaborate with other departments within the firm, to assist with streamlining processes and help deliver a high and insightful service to clients;
Work with clients to prepare applications and work with Senior Consultants to prepare annual filings required to capture negotiated incentives
Keep up to date with market developments and identify areas of risks and/or opportunities for existing and future clients.
Skills & Personal Qualities:
Knowledge and effective use of problem solving skills;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Exceptional organizational skills; able to balance multiple priorities and projects, keeping all team members informed of progress and issues;
Ability to work on own initiative and as part of a team;
Self starting work ethic;
Emphasis on quality and accuracy (attention to detail);
Places a priority on developing own knowledge and skills;
Excellent interpersonal communication and relationship building skills;
Ability to support and grow new hires into the practice
Requirements
Bachelors degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field preferred;
3+ years of consulting experience, preferably in corporate tax, finance; State and Local Tax or Incentive experience a plus;
Strong knowledge and proficiency with spreadsheet and presentation software including Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook).
Physical Requirements
Involves work of a general office nature; typically includes extended periods of sitting and/or operation of a computer
Regularly required to talk, hear, and use hands and fingers to write and type
Ability to speak clearly so others can understand you
Ability to read and understand information and ideas presented orally and in writing
Ability to communicate information and ideas in writing and orally so others will understand
Regularly required to utilize vision abilities, allowing reading of printed material, graphics, and computer displays
Some travel will be required
